2009 Season

Played in 18 games and made 17 starts … Scored her first collegiate point at Kennesaw State when she assisted on Katie Scott’s goal in the 64th minute of the Owls win over Alabama A&M (9/20) … Recorded her second, and most significant, assist of the season in the opening round of the Atlantic Sun Conference Women’s Soccer Championship when she contributed on Caitlin Dingle’s game-winning, extra-time goal against Jacksonville (11/5).

2008 Season

Played in 14 games for the Owls as a freshman... Had her first shot on goal in a 4-1 win over USC Upstate (10/19)... Totaled two shots and one shot on goal in 249 minutes.

Prep Career

Spent her High School career at Ontario’s Country Day, where she helped her team win CISA and CISAA National Tournaments three years in a row and was the team captain for three years... Led her team in goals for three years...Received Outstanding Athlete Award from the city of Richmond Hill in 2007... Inducted into the city's Hall of Fame in 2008... Played club for the Richmond Raiders for three seasons... Won the Canadian National Championships in 2007... Played for Team Ontario for three years.

Personal

Born in Ontario, Toronto... the daughter of Melanie and Peter Gibson... Has one sister, Sjorland... Favorite athlete is her cousin, Cassie Campbell, who is captain of the women's Canadian Olympic hockey team... Is a Psychology major...In her spare time, she likes to go running, play tennis and go shopping... Currently playing on her IPod is Incubus' "Dig"...

Thais talks about her assist on the game-winning goal in last year's A-Sun semifinals
